eenspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/31/03 2:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3084.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Does Begging add Taunt?</span><hr size=1> Sorry for the newbie question.<br>
I assume begging doesn't add any aggro, but a war friend of mine say it does....<br>
<br>
Can anyone answer my question?<br>
<br>
Thanks. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilaara>Kilaara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 251<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/31/03 3:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3084.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does Begging add Taunt?</span><hr size=1> When you wanna know if begging makes mobs aggro .. sure but only the miss.<br>
<br>
That would mean that the lower your begging skill is the more aggro would it bring to you.<br>
<br>
But were talking here about a very very small amount of aggro.<br>
<br>
Maybe its 3 to 5 Points ... not more.<br>
<br>
And when youre in skill &gt; 150 ... the effect is not noticeable any more.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:lime;font-size:x-small;">Da Basherle</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4552"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:gold;font-size:small;">Kilaara Drachenfliege</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Drachentänzer</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Kael Drakkel</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dakkin2>Dakkin2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/31/03 3:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3084.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does Begging add Taunt?</span><hr size=1> Well ... technically he's right and you're wrong.  Unsuccessful begging (i.e. usually when your skill is fairly low) does add a very little hate.<br>
<br>
The amount seems to be so small however that most people don't bother to use it, especially since you have to take attack off to do so.<br>
<br>
So in the context of combat and taunting, I'd say you're right and he's wrong; beg adds so little hate it's not noticeable that I've seen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=beornegarfrostwolf>Beornegar Frostwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/31/03 11:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3084.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does Begging add Taunt?</span><hr size=1> Some people claim that the aggro generated by begging is not transferred to other mobs the same way that combat aggro is, thereby making it possible to pull using beg rather than an attack and get fewer adds.  I have no idea whether or not this actually works and if so in what circumstances it's effective.  Just something I've read on the boards in the past, never seen any data to confirm or deny it.<br>
<br>
Beo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khallimbloodhelm>KhallimBloodhelm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 231<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/03 3:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3084.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.ptd.net/~twyst/images/ra.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does Begging add Taunt?</span><hr size=1> Well, I know that in exp groups, when the chanter has mezzed something, I go up and taunt/beg/taunt before breaking mez.  I don't have any concrete data, but throwing in a couple begs along with the taunt seems to gain me aggro better when I break the mez. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:copperplate gothic light;font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>They come like sacrifices in their trim, <br>
And to the fire-eyed maid of smoky war <br>
All hot and bleeding will we offer them.<br>
The mailed Mars shall on his altar sit <br>
Up to his ears in blood.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:copperplate gothic light;font-size:small;">~William Shakespeare, Henry IV ~</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105780" target="top"> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://webpages.charter.net/zmorse/pics/Khallim2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aerildroigheann>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 532<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/03 3:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3084.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does Begging add Taunt?</span><hr size=1> You can do a jig and stand on your head too, but that won't make any difference either.  Beg does not add aggro.  A non-kos mob will not attack you if you beg from it, whether you succeed or fail. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:verdana;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=629229" target="top">Aeryl Firebrand</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->,  Overlord<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.freshpope.com/undaunted/" target="top">Undaunted</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, Xegony</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grimmlokk>Grimmlokk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 1114<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/03 3:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3084.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spinhead2.gif?flezbwidth=30&flezbheight=41? WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does Begging add Taunt?</span><hr size=1>  Lots of people swear begging helps. Here's my experience=P<br>
<br>
 Early in release when I was still in my teens I started begging mobs a lot just to get the skill up. Not stuff I was fighting, normal mobs. I don't think my skill ever cleared 20 or 30. Anyhow, in all that time begging 100's of times I got agro'd once(1 time, 1 less than 2), by Lucky the begger ironically... 1 point of agro is all it takes to get attacked by a non agro mob. So there ya go. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=372117"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://grimmlokk.homestead.com/files/spingrim3c.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khallimbloodhelm>KhallimBloodhelm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 233<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/1/03 3:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3084.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.ptd.net/~twyst/images/ra.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does Begging add Taunt?</span><hr size=1> Aeryl, you're wrong, actually.  I was in FV once and I begged from a gaurd I was ally to, he attacked and killed me.  But its true that begging does not (most times) aggro Non-Kos mobs.  I think some mobs are particularly antagonistic towards begging.  But begging from KOS mobs does generate aggro, in my experience.  Just think of it way, if they don't like u already, they hate it when u try and beg from them. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:copperplate gothic light;font-size:small;"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>They come like sacrifices in their trim, <br>
And to the fire-eyed maid of smoky war <br>
All hot and bleeding will we offer them.<br>
The mailed Mars shall on his altar sit <br>
Up to his ears in blood.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:copperplate gothic light;font-size:small;">~William Shakespeare, Henry IV ~</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105780" target="top"> <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://webpages.charter.net/zmorse/pics/Khallim2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aerildroigheann>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 533<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/03 8:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3084.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does Begging add Taunt?</span><hr size=1> I'm more inclined to believe that specific NPCs are hard-coded to react violently to begging, which is just the exception that proves the rule.  I mean of all the mobs that would have aggroed, it was Lucky the Beggar.  My gut tells me that's not just the RNG at work.  On top of that, beg is supposed to be a beneficial skill.  If it could fail and aggro any mob, imagine how many people would be getting slaughtered in all the newbie zones when the game was first coming out.  Didn't they even fix mend so that it wouldn't kill monks on a failure with low HPs?<br>
<br>
At any rate, I doubt that they'd bother putting that supposed tag on mobs that are going to be run of the mill exp mobs.  By that same token, you could say walking up to a mob generates aggro ... because if you're kos to that mob it will aggro on you.  Or you could say &quot;phat lewt&quot; to all the mobs for aggro because a few in PoG will attack you for it.<br>
<br>
I think this is just one of those things that if you use it, you swear by it.  If you don't, you don't see any need for it. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:verdana;font-size:x-small;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=629229" target="top">Aeryl Firebrand</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->,  Overlord<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.freshpope.com/undaunted/" target="top">Undaunted</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, Xegony</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aerildroigheann>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 4/2/03 9:01:11 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=frodlin7th>Frodlin7th</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 383<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/03 11:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3084.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does Begging add Taunt?</span><hr size=1> My current theory on begging and aggro:<br>
<br>
Certain mobs are given scripts to react to begging attempts.  Those mobs are intelligent mobs in cities or other social settings with whom you'd normally interact, such as guards, merchants, etc.<br>
<br>
The ONLY time begging appears to have a chance to add aggro is on mobs who are coded to respond to begging either positively or negatively.   In other words... if a mob reacts positively to begging (here's a copper piece now get the hell out of here), then he's also coded to respond to an unsuccessful begging attempt.   If not, then no.   So, on mobs you'd normally fight (if you're not exping off of guards, or butcherblock dorfs or gnomes), then no, begging would have ---ZERO---  effect.  If you cannot receive something from the mob, then you cannot generate aggro by a failure.<br>
<br>
If someone can show me for instance... that a Dark Elf Innorruuk worshipper who's dubious in Karnor's Castle to the dogs can aggro one by simply begging, then I'll be willing to change my tune, but I don't think it's the case.   I'll try on my necro just to be sure. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khumak>Khumak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 281<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/2/03 11:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3084.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Does Begging add Taunt?</span><hr size=1> Interesting theory Frodlin.  I suspect you're probably right.  In any case I'd be willing to bet the aggro on a beg even for the mobs it works on is fairly trivial.  My beg skill is still zero and I plan to leave it there. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=472195">Khumak</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
